main event: Ground radar detected an unidentified object at Wayside Park, Florida on May 23, 1961.
interesting points: The unidentified blip was detected for approximately 10 minutes., The object was described as having two humps and a fiery red color., Witnesses observed the object hovering and then appearing to fly out with flames., The object was visible for about 30 minutes before it faded out of sight., The object was reported under conditions of night with good visibility.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object with two humps and a fiery red light
witness description: MSgt Charles A. Baumgart, Headquarters Section, 4756th Air Base Group
